        </div>

        <p>The drive for customization doesn’t stop at home. It has reshaped the modern coffee industry, with Starbucks leading the way—turning personal preferences into a scalable business model.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="fade-in-section">
        <div class="section-title">The Starbucks Effect: Personalization at Scale</div>
        <p>Starbucks didn’t just sell coffee, it sold personalization, turning custom orders into a cultural phenomenon and offering millions of combinations on a mass scale.</p>
        <p>Explore the third visualization: The Evolution of the Starbucks Menu. Drag the slider and hover over each bar to see how the menu expanded from one basic offering in 1971 to countless customizable drinks today. Starbucks turned customization into commerce. Cold drinks now lead the market, driven by younger consumers who seek tailored experiences.</p>
        <p>This menu expansion wasn’t just about business growth, it mirrored societal changes toward greater personal choice. Starbucks transformed coffee into an experience of customization, with drinks that could be endlessly personalized through modifiers, syrups, and add-ons.</p>
        <p><em>Fun Fact:</em> In 2022, 60% of all Starbucks drinks were customized, generating over $1 billion in modifier-based revenue.</p>
        <p>Ordering a “venti oat milk caramel latte with light foam” isn’t just about taste, it’s about curating an experience. Starbucks made personalization a cultural norm, where every order is a performance of identity.</p>

        <div class="visual fade-in-section">
            <h3>Visual 3: The Evolution of the Starbucks Menu</h3>
            <div id="observablehq-viewof-starbucksVisualization-bbcc354a"></div>
