        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="fade-in-section">
        <p>Coffee’s role in identity also extends into what we share and gift, adding another layer of cultural significance.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="fade-in-section">
        <div class="section-title">Coffee as a Shared Gift: Meaning Beyond the Cup</div>
        <p>Coffee isn’t just something we consume, it’s something we give. Notice how in the timeline, each November/December, Google searches for “coffee maker” surge, even surpassing “Buy iPhone in all 50 states. Hover over the timeline and US map to see the interest breakdown in each state.”</p>
        <p>Coffee as a gift is an invitation, an experience of new flavors and meaningful moments. In a world where experiences matter more than possessions, gifting coffee says: I see you, I know your taste, and I want you to have something special. Coffee becomes a symbol of care, thoughtfulness, and shared identity.</p>
        
        <div class="visual fade-in-section">
            <h3>Visual 4: Search Trends Comparison</h3>
